{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"63def90f-1ae2-4324-a959-b25f3f26bd72","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update packages** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\nKeep your existing `xunit` 2.9.3 package reference.\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** the same way:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` v1.0.0+ is the MTP-native runner for xUnit.net.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- Your test code itself doesn't need any changes.\n- If you use `dotnet test` CLI flags specific to VSTest (e.g., `--logger`), check the [MTP docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview) for equivalent options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"11880d54-4f33-4484-a488-a014bb20ba62","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":402,"requestId":"1BD3:D7811:2031000:2390F59:6A03CE05"},"id":"63209a90-d330-49fd-b3e2-b3d01625a35f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:04:14.550Z","parentId":"0e862a1a-7432-4787-94cc-09cd5ba3f7bc"}
